name: Dim Sum Palace
reviews: [{'content': "I've been eating dim sum for over 30 years. This is the best dim sum and most authentic I've had in a long time", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '10/18/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "this place is my goto and favorite dimsum spot in flushing! almost everything is really really good & high quality with such pretty presentations -- the only one i'd skip are their soup dumplings (too thick of a skin for me). other than that, grab all your friends so you can try everything on their menu! ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/-50Fo8h6Oh_dzpzlfTJd3A/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/26/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Came for dinner a couple of times while in mid-town. name: Golden City Chinese Restaurant
reviews: [{'content': 'Really great fast take out! I got the Seasame Chicken combination plate and an egg roll it was dope', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '7/29/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "An incredibly plain, generic and kinda dumpy takeout in an area that's beginning to gentrify but still not many residents. Basically what you'd see if finding oneself in the outer boroughs. ', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '4/18/2021', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'One of the best Chinese food in town I never had a problem with them \xa0good food, I been coming hea for years always great food', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '4/3/2022', 'stars': None}]

name: Café China
reviews: [{'content': 'We had an excellent meal at Café China. Food was great--well-flavored, excellently seasoned. Service was outstanding. name: CHILI
reviews: [{'content': 'Reasonably priced. Awesome dumplings, particularly the soup dumplings! Also, first time having duck fried rice!', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '11/19/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'A cute Szechuan place with great food and even better service! The decor is amazing and gives off both traditional and homey vibes. Some of the servers were dressed in traditional Chinese attire, which was a fun touch. name: Grand Sichuan
reviews: [{'content': "My family and I have been coming here for over 20 yrs and it is one of my favorite restaurants period let alone chinese restaurants. I am a 55yrs old born, raised native NY'er in the \xa0NYC restaurant industry and my wife is Asian american and we are huge foodies who have traveled the world and trying chinese food at hundreds of other places around the world, over the years and we still faithfully return here and pretty much exclusively come here when we want the best authentic tasting chinese food/ any food imaginable. The negative reviews are either fake/ paid or written by clueless customers. Every meal and this numbers in the hundreds has always been delicious. Every friend / family that we have brung has loved it. The steamed pork soup dumplings the best ive ever had. The cold spicy chili oil beef tendon is still unique and addictive. We love the pork with dried bean curd and chinese celery, the Azou spicy chicken, the shredded steamed potatoes with vinegar and peppers. They have amazing ma-po tofu, pea shoots w garlic and many dishes here are far from average chinese resto fair. We dread the day we may move from the area or should they close that we cant enjoy their food ever again. Lastly unlike many chinese restaurants, the owners, staff and service are personable and wonderful and can treat you like family!", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '10/13/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'I love Grand Sichuan for reasons that don\'t entirely have to do with the food. \xa0They are across the street from my apartment, and if they ever closed I would be heartbroken. \xa0Lots and lots of family dinners here, and the staff treat us like family. \xa0You don\'t come for the decor, either, but the atmosphere is always warm, festive and comfortable. \xa0I saw Andrew Rannells here once picking up his to-go order back in my peak "Girls" rerun watching phase and I almost died. \xa0If it\'s good enough for Andrew, it\'s good enough for me.', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '9/15/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "I've been coming here for years so it holds a special place in my heart. \xa0They have great lunch specials, \xa0the place is a little dark with a kind staff. \xa0The place has that old school New York feel, which could also translate as worn and dirty - with character. \xa0", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '6/25/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Used to be a five star restaurant with quality food but the last two visits have not been good. Ordered dried string beans and they we okay better in past. Ordered soup dumpling seemed like thrown together with a sticky weird casing. Moo shu was gross, but first time daughter order this here and I advised against it to begin with. But it's on their menu so it's on them to cook it, but should have sent it back! All family members not feeling good after dinner I think it was the string beans as that was the common dish. Sorry with all the great options in the city I won't be back.", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '10/11/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Best spot in area for delicious soup dumplings! Be careful they come out super out so take your time eating them so you get to fully enjoy these bad boys! They melt in your mouth', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/8le-9Jc3-vs6VnCbMMg2MA/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '6/10/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Haven't been here for a while, everything stays the same. Typical average Chinese restaurant service but delicious food. We had eggplants with garlic sauce and Ma po tofu. The eggplants was better than the tofu.", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '9/28/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'The food is good American style Chinese. \xa0The 2-star rating is for the service. \xa0They have a couple of waitresses that are overly friendly with the male patrons. (Calling them boyfriends, etc.) \xa0They tend to get passive aggressive when you don\'t give the extra attention. \xa0During our last visit, we had to ask for napkins 3 times and got two of the orders wrong even after her writing it down. \xa0On two separate occasions with two different waitresses, they reluctantly wrap up the leftovers at the table and said, "Next time I\'m going to make you put away, ha-ha". \xa0We\'re done with this place and are not going back. \xa0We prefer our Moo shoo without a side of harassment!', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '10/17/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Best Chinese food I've had in Chelsea. We ordered the pork steamed dumplings, beef and broccoli (oyster sauce), and the sesame chicken!!", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/q6Y9CVs-V1DRQGIuOgsZCQ/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '6/27/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "This chicken and broccoli lunch menu was the worst chicken and broccoli i've ever had. Mushy, quality of the meat is just the worst. I feel disgusted after one bite. Brown rice also smelled funky. When I complained, the server just nodded and didn't say anything. I'm sorry for anyone that'll be getting this food in the future.", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Lhn9J7T3cYcYWuf45eor2g/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '12/29/2021', 'stars': None}, {'content': "I was really pleasantly surprised with this spot. I was dragged out here for lunch because apparently the food was good enough that someone wanted to come back after having dinner here for a quick lunch bite. I was expecting like traditional crap Chinese take out. But to be honest, rarely do I ever see legit Chinese food out of China Town (whether it be Manhattan/Queens/or Brooklyn's version of China Town) and this place is the real deal. They have soup dumplings (albeit a tiny bit more expensive here) and my dining companion had shrimp lo mein. Which I'm pretty sure shrimp lo mein is one of his only Chinese food orders he ever gets at this point. (I know this is bastardized American Chinese, I'm getting to my point). But I stole some shrimp and they were good. My soup dumplings were awesome. The dumpling skins were absolute perfection. The meat mixture and broth were delicious. I went the pork route instead of the crab meat mixed in but next time. They're definitely not frozen rest assured because I saw them hand rolling and folding dough in the distance. Definitely a diamond in the rough for Chelsea. I don't know if it's Sichuan per se. We obviously didn't explore the menu in great depth and neither of us ordered anything spicy but they have things on the menu you wouldn't see at any average run of the mill joint. I mean, I never see Xiao LongBao anywhere. So two thumbs up for that alone. God bless. I'll probably be back at some point hungover or drunk in the near and imminent future.", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/3Fy-DLfcH80WDOqcfJotBg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/QRn897qUt0ynZN5M0DpFjg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/9gDu5U_GX34wCzNTS1OTQg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/siZkpl5DRsb_SUwz--eNVA/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/25/2021', 'stars': None}]

I wish it brought more ground pork though, i felt it was very little meat. But the sauce was super flavorful!', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '8/25/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Very authentic and always delicious. Love the velvet fish here as well as most other dishes, including the tofu with crabmeat and sautéed snow pea shoots. Skip the wine. Dry pot is also tasty but a bit too expensive so we usually just stick with the other dishes.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/FyaC7Ll4xKEI8QJaDKjktw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/B6pyzv-fuhLZgELC4gyUJA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/jiXa2mzKeFEvQSVeSF-SfQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/gu3BfrRnQj4du0ku4msNrQ/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '3/13/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'I happened to have a training in the city today and I was craving for some nice Chinese food for lunch, so I searched from Yelp and recommended me this place, came here for the first try, and I was amazed by their authentic hunan flavor! First time I finished all my plates and also ordered some dishes to go for dinner to eat with my hubby tonight. Their prices were also very reasonable compared with other Chinese restaurants in the city, highly recommended!', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '9/19/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "This is my favorite dry pot place in the neighborhood! My favorite is the build your own pot where you can select the meats and vegetables as well as the spice level you'd like. I always get the pork and lotus root - the root is perfectly cooked with the right level of tenderness and crunch. I get the medium spice level and as someone who loves spicy food, it's just right for me. My friend and I split some of the appetizers, including the pork soup dumplings and scallion pancakes. The scallion pancakes are super tasty but the pork soup dumplings are a bit too thick for my taste. Overall, a solid 4.5/5 meal!", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/eGrm3gp-PANxzb0k2W-qGQ/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/14/2021', 'stars': None}]

name: Calle Dao Chelsea
reviews: [{'content': 'Fantastic food and drinks!! I came for a birthday dinner. We were about 20 minutes late for our reservation, but they were super kind, held the table for us, and seated us promptly when we arrived. ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/FiwtAR_pi4U3xkg_bFDAVA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/9tp6YGM58uV9ffklWbc5Mw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/KGylkuh1airiJsFdMQA1gQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Qd8rTbFXwUO2EEB1-al-pA/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/9/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Unique Cuban / Chinese fusion restaurant in Chelsea. I ordered the Char Siu Pork Belly, which was cooked well - crispy on the outside and tender on the inside. The main issue though was that there were only two strips of pork belly... for $34! Not the best deal... although the sweet potato puree and pineapples on the side were good.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/yqU1nm6-WnX7fSM2lGZfhw/300s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/LXSfaE3gwfcnXN0WguB15g/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/7/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Came here to meet old coworkers for dinner and had a great time! The food was delicious but my faves were the cuban fried rice and the papas rellenas! Those 2 dishes stood out the most with their flavor profile. I had the black rice paella as my main dish and although it was good, it wasn't something I would get again. I did have enough to bring home as leftovers for my garbage can, I mean sister. (: ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/_9bRtsWOX6uuTWcrqQtcCw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/FKyWS3iLgTV1eCvYf5XUsw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/vXcBOTnfQwEQHueMsdn0oA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/S-8ZFotxgxF401NZvYGSug/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '9/29/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Got seated right away even though we didnt have a reservation on friday night. They have some happy hour drinks and food during the weekdays. The mojito was good and sweet. We tried the duck bao which was tasty and you had to construct it yourself. The lechon on tostones were pretty good as well and had a lot of pork. The pork belly was a pretty big portion and tasty as well. The restaurant was cute and servers were really nice.', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '11/20/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "I've been here before but I've completely forgotten what I've eaten here. However, the two of us shared the ropa vieja noodles ($30) and the seafood black rice paella ($35), and it was some of the best fusion dishes that we've had. ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/gL8T78I7gAG7K5B7wQ2UzA/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '9/19/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Calle Dao is such a unique experience in the best way! In addition to the nice decor and the great service, the fusion of Cuban and Chinese cuisines ended up working really well. Along with drinks, we had Yucca fries, Cuban eggs benedict, ma-po maduros, crispy duck with baos, and avocado toast. Everything was amazing, but my number one goes to the Ma-po maduros. Definitely try it! It's the epitome of a perfect fusion of cuisines. My drink, Yuma, was also really refreshing and paired well with the food. ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/TE9F6T89z3gaMp9X26yIqg/300s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/PhdtJH40AKTjxvlXnhqMHQ/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/24/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Can't say I fell in love with the food but the atmosphere was lovely. Cuban sandwich spring rolls came with loads of mustard and were nice and crunchy. I also ordered a lo mein dish that was an off spin of another famous Cuban recipe.... Noodles were tender and there was a hefty portion (couldn't even finish it tbh). ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/GY1t1lG-EwqYzO3NeSq88w/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '8/20/2022', 'stars': None}]

name: Very Fresh Noodles
reviews: [{'content': 'Came to this noodle place at Chelsea Market to kill time in the evening and it was a good decision!! We ordered the tingly and spicy cumin lamb dry noodle and we were so speechless about how good the taste was since the very first bite. We are a fan of bold herbs and spices flavor and this noodle was so flavorful, a bold one (the combination of cumin and curry like flavor in a rather thick sauce consistency was amazing). They came with coriander leaves on top and there was this sour sensation as well (not sure where this came from) so it was different flavors from cumin, curry-like, fresh coriander and a bit of sourness blended. The texture of the meat was so tender. Noodle was not that chewy but was still acceptable. Portion wise, we got confused whether this was the noodle with the meat topping, or another way around since we got plenty of meat, perhaps more than the noodle itself, lol, we loved it though. Overall, enjoyable until the very last bite. ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/JdQlcbmKbxL42FHdhrHl2w/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/21/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Great noodles, good burst of flavor, the meat is beautifully seasoned with a mix of tingly and spicy flavors dancing on your tongue. The beef noodle soup is earthy and savory, with tons of umami flavor. The fat noodles lend you wanting more. The dishes are simple and pair together nicely. The seating outdoors is a nice touch with large spaces, but are limited. They can be pretty crowded but food comes out relatively quickly.', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '11/22/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'I had the Taiwanese noodles, they are tasty. The noodels that came with it are broad, flat, fresh, and delicious.', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '11/19/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'This stall inside of Chelsea Market is quite busy, but the line moves fast and the dishes come out very quickly (within 2 minutes). There is minimal seating at the counter, but there is seating outside the market as well.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/f2I_bT7N9L80fVwd3Dpt5Q/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/11/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "All I can say is wow. One of the best noodles I've ever had. 'Very Fresh Noodles' made right in front of your eyes. The wide flat freshly made noodles were chewy and spicy with that numbing tingly sensation in your mouth with every bite. You can choose between dry or soup noodles. I forgot to ask for no scallions but the noodles were sooo delicious, I ate it anyways. The spicy smashed Cucumbers had the perfect amount of spice to it and super garlicky. Loooove it!! Can't stop thinking about these noodles. Make sure you get a good front seat watching them prepare the noodles as you enjoy your food. They have a great selection of drinks to cool down the numbing spice too!", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/x66SSZLNmYCAupD9BYULIg/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/7/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Authentic handmade noodles in Chelsea Market! There's always a long line here but service is quick and efficient. I also appreciate the choice of veggie options! ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/V13Y4biEa9Gpu3Bf97j1Rw/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/5/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Yum!! This spot is worth the hype and waiting in line! It's located in the Chelsea Market and you can be sure that there's a line at all hours but don't worry as it goes by fast. We ended up waiting for about 10 minutes to order and then another 10 to receive our food which we took to eat at the tables right outside. ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/cInH3V68ZklQLP7-evcO-g/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/23/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'FAVE NOODS PLACE OF ALLLLL TIME ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Jr-2P0WPKVF2mPjH--tO1A/300s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/7SfI-n1srAqvNWb_RvbE7w/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/27/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "If you're going to chelsea's market specifically for this place, I'd recommend coming before it opens because the line gets ridiculously long. Luckily, I was hear right before it opened and didn't have to wait too long .", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/q0EvKa1EEaQZsl78TubJxA/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/25/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Years ago, when Very Fresh first opened, I came, ate and was disappointed. I was so annoyed, I forgot to write a Yelp review.", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/ruhxmIZ773YPdDTNN2rlSA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/hEc0p_REdDBkDIo7qrb10w/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/bBBRLY5AfdLxxPG7ra1gxQ/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/21/2022', 'stars': None}]

name: Wild Ink
address: 500 W 33rd St Fl 5 New York, NY 10001
reviews: [{'content': 'Was stuck between 4 and 5 because I save 5 for my favorites but I think a 5 is more fair. name: Awesum Dimsum
reviews: [{'content': 'Great casual dim sum place, one of our favourites around time square. We like everything on the menu.', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '10/15/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Unlike the traditional dim sum set up, there are no carts here. This makes sense because there's limited space for seating on a single floor. There is additional seating upstairs. ", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '10/13/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Overall the food was excellent. The exception to that was the thin noodles. Very dry. Maybe it was toward the end of the day. All the other items we ordered were excellent. I've been to another Awesome Dim Sum (on the East Side in the 20s) and I would say that one was a bit better than this location but not by much. Just the noodles which I didn't order the last time. ", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '11/22/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Super sleek dim sum place with good food. Solid option for quick lunch in a busy part of nyc close to lots of transit hubs and tourist spots. \xa0', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/htbn_kdkFDnSI-ZLTHLccw/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/19/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Amazing place for dim sum and then some!', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/lCNDmKWFOcbGD29TUHGteA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/sn76sgQ2BXcWEiTRiutrnw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/srkMmSpQLBCwVeoCp-V9Dw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/iMXEfSB2QQznsspsoYD6KA/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/6/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "If you're in the midtown area and craving decent dimsum, this is a pretty good option! I would recommend the siu mai, and the wrapped dumpling. The rice noodle was a bit too soft for my taste but I've had worse elsewhere.", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '11/25/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Order at the counter and pick up made to order dim sum. Cool concept but would not return", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/w1SE_ozWuWGs0vBzk76wGg/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/11/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Came by for breakfast with high hopes this morning and it was merely mediocre. name: Stick To My Pot Potsticker
reviews: [{'content': 'Very unusual spot for this ', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '8/11/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'I stopped by to grab a bite before my train left Penn Station. ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/IBkig4ZztPCn0coVC3qHVw/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/27/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'This 35th Street block has a couple of my favorite spots for lunch. Time to add another--Stick to My Pot Potsticker.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/SY9OdUoFnhbz0DtbosjEzQ/300s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/AU64WpoOeM1qQh0UOEvJRA/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '8/12/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'On my last visit to nyc I decided to try Stick to my Pot since it was super close to my hotel. ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/1GQMxHcVyMqfpaohT_7zIA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/ESZ455U4tNg9HEsG_amq-A/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/3PgJIoIY7gh4bb_KUEIlMg/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '8/3/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Dumplings, fresh delicious dumplings. I thought this place would be a typical dumpling joint. Guy gets frozen dumplings from the back and tosses them into a steamer. DEAD WRONG. As soon as I ordered I watched the guy behind the counter lovingly stuff, wrap and cool my custom half and half dumplings. The options are simple but elegant. A few different types of filling for the dumplings or you can mix two of them together for fifty cents or so. Options for cooking the dumplings are steamed, fried or soup for an extra dollar. I also got an order of bao for food measure. The dumplings were great and the wrapper was just thick enough to hold everything together but not too thick to be annoying. The flavor of the shrimp and pork both were noticeable with great bites of both. This place is a hidden gem and entirely worth trying. As always happy hunting', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Pg0Hi2NBICS--KTtnjTwvQ/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/14/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'I found a my new favorite lunch place. Ordered 4 dumplings and a pulled pork bao for $11! The chicken cilantro dumplings are superb. ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Fxj1aco14Pq57TMi3fVtNw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/DC8uDv4YWGsPqw69rCzMng/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/759VwEaVb5MXsqB1ttLKVA/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '4/19/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Keepin it real out here in Midtown', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/j_cYXv-0FaVpCMyFy8fnUQ/300s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/tej0DvD5AHbO3dFfD4XYtA/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '1/4/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "The chicken dumplings and shrimp dumplings are amazing here, and the shiitake mushrooms in the spring rolls are so good too. They are constantly making fresh dumplings- fresh fillings scooped into wontons. They have constant turnover so everything is hot and fresh. I can see why so many people frequent this shop. Prices are reasonable for what you're getting too", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '9/1/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Saw the cooks pulling some dumplings out of frozen bags. In addition, the classic pork dumplings mix was made fresh but severely undercooked. Found a couple raw pieces of pork and could not finish. ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/wGbGY9KblxqMtUYTBn903w/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '6/23/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Absolutely love their dumplings,noodles and spring rolls.Most importantly- all is freshly made and you can see the cook preparing the dish you ordered.', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '9/27/2022', 'stars': None}]

name: Excellent Dumpling House
reviews: [{'content': "So so so good. If you want a local dim sum place with nonsense service. Go here. It's worth it. ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/1Pf-wuIvfTqU74_jQa895g/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '8/19/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "I've been to Excellent Dumpling House a couple times and it's always been a reliable spot for Chinese food. Today we ordered to go - two lunch specials, xiaolongbao, and pork potstickers. ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Zr-tcLfqvHUaDzAgx2sRzQ/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/21/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Pros- Seated very quickly and the food is authentic. Prices are reasonable and variety of food to choose from. There were a lot of customers flowing steadily, which is always a good sign. We ordered some vegetable spring rolls, an order of chicken fried rice, and an order of pork soup dumplings. All of the food was very delicious and the portions were great since we were sharing for a party of two.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/FQ0kAjIdk6H9JQh5yUoDFQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/R-s5ZNiIJjeJJNjrk8vkxQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/_Ey3LjT4-j_AbXmdbLbesA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/wkv1aFdP_vkiUFc6CIppBw/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/15/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Nice spot for dim sum and other Chinese favorites. The dim sum menu wasn't super expansive but it did get the job done. I got the crab xia Long which the waiter said was most popular. It's a soup dumpling and it was good but I didn't get any crab flavor from it. I also got the steamed chicken dumplings which were just ok. name: Hutaoli Music Restaurant & Bar
reviews: [{'content': 'Love this place! Celebrated a handful of birthdays and events here. Live music, outstanding food, and beautiful decor, not much more to ask for!', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/U4RrpPN-VLQLTJCsKtovLA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/heHKhI2AM-QNQjH7ZU8eiQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/OCw6sePRnDVyGm-VEaLWzw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/NLYPXJbDND_JcTDSYoHcWQ/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/30/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'I met 2 of my friend for dinner. They had made the reservation through the phone. The restaurant is uniquely decorated. Very trendy, there is a stage and movie screen where they have live performances throughout the evening. Take note it is extremely loud, I mean loud! The food was very good. The service was extremely lacking. ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Z2Tsoq-TLr8R1KUWMGJ2Hw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/-6RfdRFZ42rzJjxfoh4dPw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/2VLmYM6tjIqbs5fXgh4NoQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/4r9LedWtwUB10OK58UK3zw/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/7/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "It has been a while since I've been torn about a place. Food and drinks are great, but jeez does it take a long time to get them. I came here the first time for a rehearsal dinner for a dear friend of mine. We were a party of many people so I gave them a break then, but the second time I went, I went for dinner. Not sure if they are short on staff or what have you, but I was insanely hungry by the time my food came out. However, would recommend this place for authentic Chinese food if you are in the area and want Chinese food. ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/cmSbKEzFR2H-wsfW9UlyaA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/OUOnvo-SnLnAzeqV26m_RA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/EeUUU5iA2hV_LS1oXvkItQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/2Wd9C4e4PZktIs1AWUynjg/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '9/20/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'A fun and lively spot with live performances. There was a fried potato dish that was incredible!! Great spot to come with a group and share a bunch of dishes.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/bWVzu3U5uDz_NCVeHxi08w/300s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/IIJBtYpfOQ1gv_bj5kAOmA/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '9/29/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Visited here for the ambiance, but turns out the food is surprisingly good too! Came here on a Saturday night with reservations, but arrived early and without the full party, so asked to sit at the bar area. Staff was super accommodating and said we could sit in the lobby seats while we ordered a drink and waited another 30 minutes for our friend before finally asking to sit inside. Such a pretty place, whether in the lobby, the main dining hall, or what we could see of the second floor. Decor is definitely for plant lovers!', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/6JqgXoqGHQUemEBA9yqHZA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/9ep15SEjruZ1phBWfFO30Q/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/IhbkCrbJX8uLst0C0qTDIA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/JLFvst-V2wRpobeyi4Q6qw/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '6/16/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "I took one star off because it's so hard to waive any server or get their attention. So there is a bit of a wait between getting seated and getting your order in. If you wanna order like a second round of food, good luck. ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/KxbQoJj0ut_GdNM90S7PiQ/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '7/20/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Really beautiful restaurant with delicious traditional Chinese food. Walking in, you're transported to a fairy world with wispy tree branches and wooden chairs. There's a lot of servers greeting guests and serving tables. The menu is huge and has something for everyone. We came in a big group of 15 and I was in charge of ordering for the table. Some favorites were the garlic eggplant stir fry, the sour veggie fish stew, the cumin spicy lamb chops, chili crab seafood pot, shrimp tofu casserole. Everything was presented well and came out piping hot. The portions were big enough for everyone to share and get a bite. The live music was great but it did get hard to talk across the table. The drinks were very unique and tasted great.", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '10/8/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Came here with two others for my birthday on a Monday night. The place was walk in friendly for a 6pm dinner. We were original seated right next to the kitchen, which we did not like so we asked to be moved a bit farther away. We ordered the clams, potatoes, the crab and tofu, a veggie dish, and a dry hot pot. All the food was amazing, especially the crab and tofu dish. I've never had anything like that and I typically don't even like crab but it was soooo good that I bit down on the spoon a couple of times. The potatoes were a let down. It was a bit too oily to eat, but we did finish most of it. The highlight of the night was having live music accompany our dinner. The singer had an amazing voice and repertoire of songs to share with us. All in all, a well rounded meal with good company, food, entertainment and flexibility. I would recommend", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/GhlEGnyBw7UiFxmQfIfQSA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/CQWB1uJ-ZaNdXvsKp6aTpw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/89636r28YPv5nkFzNBzdZQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/PgUeAGPeskBBNRh41oQuvA/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '9/13/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Hutaoli Music Restaurant & Bar was certainly an unique place! \xa0There were plants everywhere, making it feel like an upscale Rainforest Café, décor-wise. \xa0 They offered live music nightly, with a female pianist performing on the evening of our attendance. \xa0She was very talented and played and sang both Chinese and American tunes. \xa0During her breaks, music videos played on a giant screen behind the stage. \xa0The friendly staff seemed focused on producing an enjoyable experience.', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '7/23/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Ambiance and decor is so beautiful. Staff is super attentive and friendly. Came here with a group of friends for lunch so I wasn't able to experience the live music. But I'll definitely be back during dinner service. All the dishes was very delicious and flavorful but very small portion so you definitely need to order 2-3 of them to share for a big group. Everything is mild and spicy if you like spicy. My favorite dish was the honey shrimp it was very well cooked and you can definitely taste the honey sweetness in the shrimp. Next time I'll be coming back to try the Peking duck!", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/eW5KFl9Nx-y0mONCktrixA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/v2A-4U-evQFQEoPkBBkTcg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/wUzb2gRGFdpwned7EbgQkw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/jDC-ucRFc0LHa18smQnj5A/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '8/31/2022', 'stars': None}]

If it were 30 blocks north I would eat here all the time, but being this close to Chinatown I really can't stomach paying twice the price at little alley that I would pay there ", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '11/12/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "This cute restaurant is a must stop for if you're nearby. The soup dumplings have an al dente like texture complementing the warm soup and filling inside. The braised yellow croaker is definitely a heavier dish with all the tasty sauce the slather on. I was initially surprised when the soft shell crab with rice came out with rice cakes but it worked just as well with them being nicely chewy like a gummy worm but savory. I am always a huge fan of pork belly so of course I had to get the dong po pork which SLAPPED. I feel like this combination of dishes was in the heavier side so maybe try some other lighter dishes. For the drinks, the cucumber in the class 3-2 came out very nice and refreshing while the moulin rouge was sweet with the dab of raspberries. reviews: [{'content': 'We had a great lunch here Sunday 11/19/22. China River did an excellent job accommodating our group. Depending on the time, we had 12-17 people on their second floor. It just need a bit more seasoning but, it was tasty with the chicken dishes. name: Mr. Sun
reviews: [{'content': 'Overall, a phenomenal spot to get Peking duck. Some limitations to the food, which does not detract from its overall 5/5 experience.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Rx1EnDpPemqBichxYx9bUw/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/25/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Mr. Sun us deceiving on the outside because when you walk in the door the restaurant is much larger than you would expect. We were seated right near the front immediately without a reservation. Being in the location it's in, prices here aren't the cheapest Chinese food you can get but it was pretty decent based on my first visit. A couple vegan/veg options but they do have a solid assortment across their other dishes. ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/h2zz6ofdkOk0p47L_wirJA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/aVtBMuoHSe7EqZa9eR_oNw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/ri2qNjB0Y3Ae2i_YpvBpjA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/f_JwU1Yu0mePjBMle6bjUg/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/17/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Great Pecking duck, best I've had outside of Flushing. Though, to be fair, I hardly ever order this dish. ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/5Uk286JH2WaFlJzKLIluQg/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/3/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'The half Peking duck is a big enough portion for two', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/7JnULw0IbeMOVbI4011cLQ/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/30/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "The interior was roomy and lovely, especially the large back area, which had fairy lights and pretty decor. My intention was to share the Half Peking Duck ($49) with my friend, so upon entering, I let the hostess know. The Peking Duck arrived to the table quickly. However, the person I was with didn't want to share it and I wasn't willing to pay full price for it, so I ordered something else. The Peking Duck looked pretty good and there was a decent amount of it, but the skin didn't appear to be that crispy.", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/RIHA65KtFT-sPokEr10m0g/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/HDLFQaaz0BgatA-AHyVJQg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/p6Mf9jhhQqlM4WsBxAMRHg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/8AyAbP-17atJ77SR5Cy_iQ/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '9/6/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "This place continues to be one of my favorite Chinese places in the city. It's a bit unassuming given it's in Midtown. I love that you can generally always walk in without a reservation.", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Y_nZEZYAlh4FBTIvmZDTow/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/1ZNwnwCuZnM-ssWizXgABg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/TfOMXgvlAyoLwq5V_n-IEQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/LVqkRO_5s_O-740sA6Q7jw/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '9/5/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'We went to Mr. Sun during an off hour, so the inside was empty. There were few customers coming to pick up their to-go orders. They had a nice counter seats near the entrance, and tables opposite from the counter along the wall. At the back, they had a larger room with more tables there.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/-hUmJ3sYmJqheCx1OfRnbA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/6YnKk-2Q5RqKyBbb4fzc1A/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/_Ezw2iSvrzq9k2VniOUOTw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/ilS4e6hhpquixrYvIFdw3Q/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '8/5/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "I'm only in town for a few days and just wanted some custard buns (admittedly after already having a full meal with work earlier.) I also ordered shrimp dumplings to get to an order minimum, and the sesame balls because they were 2 for the price of 1. It was all SO good. I ate almost an entire extra meal I didn't plan to eat. Honestly has been a long time since I've been this happy with a meal (and it was Postmated to me in the rain so I imagine it's even better in person.) Super impressed (and full!!)", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/LQYxSy3T-fILBdsr9YWMNg/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/17/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "We were starving after a local yoga class, and randomly peeked into Mr. Sun on a Saturday afternoon. Pretty good food and decent portions, though a little pricey for what you get, if you're not dining and splitting with a larger group. ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/5JnHWR_8eoBSBvvkd2xfUw/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '7/14/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "I felt that this restaurant would be good but wasn't too impressed with my lunch order. I got the shredded beef with peppers and brown rice -and it was quite greasy. Instead of having gravy which was expected, it was none actually- just oil. With the smaller portions restaurants are now giving , the amount of oil in this small serving was unnecessary. Yet another reason coming why come into the office is pointless- you get bad lunch. I tried, smh", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Y9oKrnWZq5ShNZGYNQDxng/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/9/2022', 'stars': None}]

name: Dim Sum Chelsea
reviews: [{'content': 'Amazing. I stopped in for a quick snack to hold me over til dinner..and I just wanted to stay here and eat everything. I got the shrimp and chive dumplings and they were pack with big and juicy shrimp and pan fried to perfection. I also got the wontons in spicy sauce and the spicy sauce was the perfect amount of heat and flavor with the consistency of the dumpling being so good. ', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '10/13/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Went for dim sum on Sunday mid-day. Not busy, and no wait. The menu has a collection of dim sum, soup, and entree-sized items. \xa0The dim sum is heavy on the dumplings, and light on everything else dim sum, so keep that in mind! \xa0We got crab and pork soup dumplings, shrimp sui mai, scallion pancake, bbq pork buns, hot and sour soup, wonton/egg drop soup, and orange flavor beef. \xa0They have a full bar, but we just had soft drinks. \xa0', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '10/24/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Walking around Chelsea market and found the dumpling place closed...looked up dim sum in the area and this placed popped up. Not very busy....so about hesitant. We tried it anyway and this was worth the walk from the market! ', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '7/11/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Came here for a super quick bite before meeting friends for drinks. This was the only restaurant that could take me with no wait so I decided to give it a shot and I will say, it was great! Started off with a nice cold Sapporo which was served very promptly. For food, I \xa0got some soup dumplings and chicken lo mein. The soup dumplings were piping hot and delicious. The quantity of lo mein was enormous! My plate was piled high with the noodles, chicken, and veggies. They definitely didn't skimp on any accord. I feel like sometimes restaurants try to make up for a lack of quality with an increased quantity, but that was definitely not the case here. The lo mein was amazing! Service was great also which rounded out this wonderful experience. Would love to return! The staff even charged my phone since it was about to die.", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/4IqrIu79f7NySud0-rir5A/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/16/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Party of 2 around 4:30ish.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/wivgSKsNYAc1wXjo_TX3sQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/IzxopgUCccrDLi4rWlM6bg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/hnJtxgJqRoET545Yap3saQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/DfgaMzLGCQbnTO1RMNI4IQ/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/12/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Came for dinner and ordered the veggie steamed dumplings, shanghai pan fried pork puns, crab and pork soup dumplings, the shangxi biangbiang noodles and cumin spiced beef. The food was all good, but lacking in overall flavor besides the cumin spiced beef. The noodles were extremely salty and the cumin beef was good but a bit chewy. The portions were as expected and the service was pretty quick. Overall a decent spot.', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '9/29/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Extra star because this place is such a value meal in addition to being very tasty! I would definitely recommend ordering the hot and sour soup. I ordered the garlic eggplant lunch combo which was only $12 (and came with the soup), and it lasted me 2.5 meals! It is slightly on the oilier side for my taste, but the flavor was great, and there were plenty of vegetarian options. Overall, an enjoyable experience from a price, taste, and distance standpoint.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/WTh3qrwCGRUFTXQT55LnGQ/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '7/23/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "We really enjoyed some of the items we had here - the Mongolian beef especially was fantastic. Unfortunately some of the items weren't very good like the Crystal shrimp dumplings (just an over cooked piece of shrimp in a rice wrapper with no seasoning or dumpling sauce.) I think I would've enjoyed the experience more but the service was just awful. We were seated right away but it took over 20 minutes for someone to bring a menu. It also took a long time to get utensils, plates, drinks and the check. There were several waitresses and only 5 occupied tables but no one appeared to be assigned to a particular table which I think caused confusion. Honestly we've had much tastier dim sum at home (Philly) so I wouldn't go out of my way to go to this place again when visiting NY even if the service was good but given the poor service it's a definite no for me.", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/LdaD2UBj0IiU_89oZhZcbw/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '6/13/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Good spot for dim sum in Chelsea when you don't want to go all the way to Chinatown or Flushing! ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/EmtC2D9p-PZJ8MuosAL_JA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/XrMfBH8HEercfjF9U8qGkQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/o2Vx0BVdXKyCZWYjs_lgdA/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/4/2021', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'We were looking for a place to grab a quick bite and stumbled upon Dim Sum Chelsea. The food to our surprise was very good! We loved the Spicy Wontons and Pork Soup Dumplings. Both came out hot and was prepared well. The braised beef noodle soup broth was layered with flavor and was super comforting given the cold weather outside. ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/btPuNu9rn21ybgoKL6evpA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/q2s7pAd-FYv4RzSYngdAhg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/3GgRp6a4t-x0SZDeBmEhzQ/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '12/18/2021', 'stars': None}]

name: Hao Noodle Chelsea
reviews: [{'content': "Keto is done. name: Shanghai Mong
reviews: [{'content': "Came here last year and would've given it five stars then but alas! Things seem to have changed. ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/3sNfi87UUBuDhP6XqpDbpQ/300s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/vSZo9Zp3JYng_FJmjPwMww/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/22/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Went to Shanghai mong the other day and want to get some nice soup. My jjamppong soondubu was really tasty and flavorful with spiciness . My boyfriends soup which was the Pho was not so much. The beef was clumped up in a grounded beef way and pretty chewy compared to actual Vietnamese spots. \xa0', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/8y4a22If4kSoPTjuSxc8Zw/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/2/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "I used to be a fan of Shanghai Mong's food ever since they opened their business(Owner changed recently).", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '9/16/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'This place is definitely a go-to for college-aged people like myself. It\'s one of the few restaurants that\'s open late, has a great menu, and fast service. The food is pretty good too. The prices are reasonable and the atmosphere is very fun. I will always return back here! My only complaint is that I\'m nearly positive they used to have Pad Thai on the menu, however, when I came back, I saw there was only "Thai Noodles". They were still good but I would much rather have the Pad Thai. For a Korean place to even offer this is still more than I can ask for.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/UER1mSnYLPJRlkCBxh_AYw/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/4/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "We had a very good dining experience here with the family. We chose the outdoor patio seating on a relatively cold day since we had a pet along. The hostess made sure we were warm and comfortable and even got a water cup and a cushion for our pet. We ordered the spicy vegetable noodles, vegetable dumplings, spring rolls and pad Thai all of it tasted good and not too greasy or heavy. We ordered the Orange Chicken which was off putting and could have done without. But that didn't take away from the overall experience.", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '11/26/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'AVOID. AVOID. AVOID.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Lfk6URD-J2LmQMfqj_3jHQ/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '7/2/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Probably the worst example of Korean Chinese food. Tourist trap, but at least its open 24/7?', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '11/5/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'I ordered the spring rolls and sesame chicken. Both were flavorless and no much more than fried dough \xa0 Both were fried in rancid oil and the chicken had no sauce on it so it was inedible. \xa0I had to throw it out as it was disgusting ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/BP_JaVqUH8luYhLe5W1lUQ/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/14/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Great place of jjajangmyun. I came with two other friends and we each ordered jjajangmyun and then shared the sweet and sour pork. I really enjoyed it and we also got fortune cookies at the end of the meal too. We did also get free spring rolls for checking in on Yelp, but I didn't think that was too great.", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/rBwwg-RQ-V0oeBV8wAdOuw/300s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/3pA9Ga7_OfRFfW0IWATuAQ/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '6/7/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Ordered jja jang myun for delivery via uber eats, which was a great dish to satisfy the jja jang myun craving. The noodles and sauce were packaged in separated containers, so you can add just as much such as you'd like. One order was a good portion size for the price, and the noodles were chewy and tasty. The sauces was flavorful but not overly salty, and there was plenty for all the noodles. All in all, a great place for jja jang myun. Can't speak to other dishes as this was all I got, but I would want to reorder or stop by and try out other options!", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '9/5/2022', 'stars': None}]

name: New Dynasty Chinese Restaurant
reviews: [{'content': "I haven't gotten cheap Chinese takeout for a looong time. ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/kVuZVas_Q7OhBJ_OakmVdQ/300s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Koyr-WRzHnsOygrpSP7QMw/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/10/2021', 'stars': None}, {'content': "So. today I wanted to get some Chinese food and I was really not trying to push myself about getting Chinese food here in New York City. Not very good from my last experience here where I was food poison. So, a number of problems happen here, 1) trying to get in the restaurant was a pain with one door for entry and exit with luggage - \xa02) there was a guest claiming he order food from 2 nights ago and has been asking from what I was hearing about a return or an order here never received. When it came time for me to order I'd asked for D1 which was the daily special with Tofu. My order took 17 minutes and 33 seconds to cook up when I was told it will take 5 minutes. Many customers came and went and I was still in the shop waiting for my food. When I received my food, I was never shown what it look like or how it was prepared. Now once at a safe place to eat it, I never send tofu the way it was prepared. It didn't taste like tofu and didn't look like tofu at all. At first, it looked like shrimp and I was hoping it was until taking my first bite and my brain and stomach will not identify the food at all. ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/vjW8H1-U9CIh_6jDuJTwgA/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '1/20/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'I found a Roach \xa0in my rice. So disgusting!!!!!!!!!!!! This place needs to shut down immediately', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/7hSmzLzEn7CQ9B5CvWoaxQ/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '2/13/2021', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'good portions, good service. Food is standard Chinese takeout food', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/9dOZEvPLtSkWQcBQ-qOjpw/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '3/21/2021', 'stars': None}, {'content': "it's fire, best spot in the city for take out of course. they're always on time, never late. food is always good!", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '2/23/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Was looking for a place for good Chinese takeout that was close to where I lived, and this place was definitely the right choice. I ordered online for pickup and got there in around 10 minutes and my food was ready for me. They have a great after 4pm deal where you get the perfect portion size with your choice of regular or fried rice and the choice between a few appetizers for an amazing price. name: Ollie’s Sichuan
reviews: [{'content': 'Had a lunch with my friend. \xa0The food was not bad. \xa0Given this location (very close to port authority) the price was good. Not to much services. \xa0We found hard to get a person to our table when wanted to order additional food. ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/zEzEtSP_HbR1BI0A7fER_Q/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '9/17/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Attentive and efficient services, \xa0Chinese traditional decor. Was treated and served very quickly. The soup dumplings brought me back to the time I was in shanghai they were very well flavored and juicy and very messy like they are supposed to be. The beef soup lacked in flavor it was listed as Spicy on the menu but had no spice. The beef was also very fatty.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/zYoMQiNW41CjzcYRiZJNtA/300s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/b-JozfU-G2QNWYGFCoF7tg/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '9/9/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Incredible Sichuan restaurant in midtown, we found out about this place from a coworker who is from Sichuan, China and he himself loves to cook so you know it's legit! I would even take my family out here and they are not easily impressed since good Chinese food is hard to come by. name: Nan Xiang Xiao Long Bao - Manhattan
reviews: [{'content': 'Dumplings were so good that you wanted to order some more. The soup inside the dumpling is very savory. I liked this place. ", 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '11/10/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "3.5 / 5.0 - Nan Xiang Xiao Long Bao is a good option to come with a group of people, since they have a spacious dining area and a large reasonably priced menu, perfect for sharing. name: ICHIRAN Midtown
reviews: [{'content': 'If you are looking for a really unique and authentic experience, this is the place! Despite the long wait, it was totally worth it and the line moves pretty fast. ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/QyI2bCC5HnWvMh-Wzr2RJg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/yVCfk5VuWa2Pz1GzV5i-ag/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/WK__thG-AfAZw4mxYt8dhQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/H2NvMOZdPggQ4nOLQG207w/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/26/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Awesome Authentic Japanese ramen shop. They make the Tonkotsu (pork broth) style of Ramen. ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/zPS0F6PY4LvJ-7oylic6TA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/V6X5Pk7HXTC6FqTiS_gezQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/xxqJrbZrPbw2a3dtkPP04g/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/tsUmi71aeWyENw1t0LBOuw/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/26/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Come here for the ramen booth experience in NYC! ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/pAQlHCG6UUX57tub9OABcg/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/22/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Every trip to Japan, Hong Kong, or New York, I always make sure to go to Ichiran. It's a very popular spot for an authentic Japanese dining experience", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/TJaAWuHjvaZIYZHzV3IP7Q/300s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Fi_8w7NaX3epggMxuay4pA/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/17/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "WHOA! This is by far the best ramen I've had in my life. The broth!!! So good. Ichiran is right in the heart of midtown Manhattan (very close to MSG) and very popular! ", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/X9LtUwzjI61t8Ar4w1U_LQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/O1ED3detBoZ7pJrv7GCNwg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/oY53MIMKDeFUsIWYassfKw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/DiEHgXEZ-IjkgOESi15yww/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/17/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Ever since I saw Ichiran on Tik Tok, it has been on my bucket list of places to try. When I saw that they have a location in New York, I was excited to be able to try them. When we arrived, there was a long time that took us about an hour wait. While waiting, the employee gave us a menu to start looking at what we wanted to order. When we sat down, another employee lifted up the curtain and took our order. The restaurant had a list of rules and suggestions. ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/5Mznccd6__g44iZoWi25wg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/V_VUIs6Fot8m9eL4mUI84A/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/iRRajvxeIk0PznVlzajZIQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/DYC0zwOvxQTSvYFZtQgkaw/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/20/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'The BEST ramen I have ever had in the US! The broth is so rich, flavorful and bold. It is so simple, yet so flavorful. Loved the whole concept of it. Very easy! Def a solo lunch or dinner is perfect. Will be back!', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/TzccraQdla9GphGTDyatYg/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/20/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'Ichiran is my favorite ramen of all time. Except, not this one. This one does the Japan chain a little dirty with their mediocre broth and unreasonable prices. ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/GqGvC0jAptdpfk_pKmfiUQ/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '10/17/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "Honestly lives up to the hype! I'm not even a ramen person because the broth can get heavy or too rich for my preference but since I've been here- I can see why everyone's obsessed and why it's my standard. The broth is so pure and rich yet light. You get to customize the dashi or saltiness of the soup and spice level in addition to your noodle texture. The service is great, it's quick and easy and simple. Lastly the ambiance is great. It's not super noisy where you can't enjoy the meal alone or with friends in a casual manner. Would recommend and would come back when I'm in NYC.", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/wMUR9ept0u_h3N93wvluzA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/KQW8RSFkVIcAmpjcbcaaqw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/OdPq8H3UqM9Cabc13wsnDQ/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/10/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'I got here at around 6pm and waited about 30 minutes before I was seated. I recommend getting here early because there are no reservations and also 20 minutes after I joined the line the line got even longer.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Qb3hexi-4Qh4JhUu2cnylQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/XM5Xay9PYpiPboyAvTHh-Q/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/UP0oICzSEoKsU_RLPC3pJg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/b_-QrmYdUYN3fzzsOagQGg/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '9/26/2022', 'stars': None}]

name: Dim Sum Palace
reviews: [{'content': 'This dim sum was some of the best I have had in the city. Definitely rivals Chinatown food. I would go back every year I come for my trade show.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/4hW_Oqcgglmw-HwKMW_AZA/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '11/12/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'I came here with four friends, and we really enjoyed this spot! It was a rainy evening and other restaurants were full, but they were able to seat us right away :)', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '11/24/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'My friend and I were so excited to try vegetarian dim sum dishes and these were pleasant but not standout. We got 2 Vegetarian Dim Sum Platters, each of which included 2 of the Buddha Delight Dumplings (green pea on top), Mixed Mushroom Dumplings (purple skin), Bamboo Shoot Dumplings (open top), and another. These were definitely very wholesome and designed carefully with a mind for fillings, but they were all quite bland and the tasteless sticky rice got tiring. The purple Mixed Mushroom Dumplings were our favorite because they were more meaty and juicy. We also got Sweet Sesame Balls which were great.', 'creator': None, 'images': [], 'review_date': '11/26/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "The dim sum is good and service is stellar, but I'm giving 5 stars for the mapo tofu dish. Silky and divinely smooth tofu~ (please excuse the low quality of the pic, it does the dish no justice)", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/EcOEiYcFATmmKAmmnba1Mg/300s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/G01tMVFfXe5LqrPI_BSWFQ/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '9/19/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'This is such a good spot to come with friends and order different items off the dim sum menu. It lets you try a lot of different dishes, so my friend and I got 4 different menu items to try. We ended up finishing all of it and feeling really full after.', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/XrmQ2iD2BeGO1hQ-fpX4ew/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/zVGOkFDXBFqtxvpSnC780A/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/lSFnXEiRPkhwwfz_3zB5pw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/FaSqfiaVT-H6Ca1GFM4PVQ/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '6/18/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "We LOVE dim sum, so any time we're in a big city, we always try to hunt down a good 7 day a week dim sum place. This time around, we tried Dim Sum Palace, and I'm glad we did.", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Ie6m0jM5-iXoT_yBYG22Tw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/X007M87ya0H6ZxkUMqHF8A/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/_TYb4mzFkcgofgMvkS52GQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/XmWoWWzJwZRayCw2ohrtPQ/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '4/25/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': "This place is a few blocks from my work. Ventured here with a co worker a day we were craving some dumplings. It's a bit expensive for dim sum but it's nyc so I guess that's what you get. I ordered the pineapple and cheese wontons and the bbq pork buns and traded one of my pork buns to my co worker for a pan fried one. They were all delicious so I wasn't that upset about the higher price haha. Wontons were crunchy and filling was creamy with a hint of pineapple. Bbq pork to bun ratio was perfect and the bbq flavor was very tasty. Pan fried dumpling had a nice crispness on the outside and filling was also tasty. Would def come back and try other items.", 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/owXL4n8rsotHl6EZDtn_vw/300s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/r5A2GaQVCaWK3S-Wh1egyA/300s.jpg'], 'review_date': '7/24/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'A huge thumbs up for this place! The food is so amazing \xa0and the staff is friendly and helpful. The dumplings are delicately made and every bite is delicious. The desserts were also great and just as good as the main courses. Everything was tasty and made my family and I want to come back. Definitely recommend!', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/yZ54XJowAIvfZLGh-O3ujA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/8B6rj1aRd7tWUs22hn_IfA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/PjJMcGaNdjMBJxQhgXFuYA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/YoPxLdmOZ5t5EpwlNdCa4Q/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '7/13/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'This was my first time trying Dim Sum and I really enjoyed the experience. I was handed a paper with many Dim Sum options and had to indicate which items I wanted to order. We decided to go with 5 items and share between 2 of us and it was plenty of food! The inside of the restaurant was nice and clean, and the staff were great. ', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Scvm5DVE1V2P0mFR3GsZBg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/3s1qAzXxHhmXPozxAOwMMw/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Qvy32GyE2RohdyVhMoksRg/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/MKMSfXjpJkpMFEnQIsjGOQ/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '2/5/2022', 'stars': None}, {'content': 'We really liked this place! The staff was really nice and the dim sum was good! We liked that they give you a paper menu with pictures and descriptions of each dim sum dish that you can check off what you want to order, instead of verbally listing everything. The pan fried tiny bun was my absolute favorite! Also really liked the 5 spice duck! I would have loved to try other things, but our bellies can only hold so much food. I would definitely return!', 'creator': None, 'images': ['https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/y1wFxPlTru9csuP43-KzzQ/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/6ck_Jwks8PPd7aVgW5ZVbA/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/JjtwaD8nLBA1_WyHGYPp7g/180s.jpg', 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/PnyyS7HWD7185GmbO6n8IA/180s.jpg'], 'review_date': '7/30/2022', 'stars': None}]
